msgid_plural "who funs"
msgstr[0] "河粉"

#. ~ Conditional name for {'str': 'hor fun', 'str_pl': 'hor fun'} when
#. COMPONENT_ID matches mutant
#: .\items\comestibles\meat_dishes.json
#, c-format
msgid "hexed %s"
msgid_plural "hexed %s"
msgstr[0] "被诅咒的 %s"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'hor fun', 'str_pl': 'hor fun'}
#: .\items\comestibles\meat_dishes.json
msgid ""
"Indo-Chinese very wide, thin noodles, fried with eggs, meat, seafood, and 3 "
"types of soy sauce."
msgstr "印度支那风味的极宽薄面，与鸡蛋、肉类、海鲜和三种酱油一起炒制。"

#: .\items\comestibles\meat_dishes.json
msgid "Babylonian beet stew"
msgid_plural "Babylonian beet stew"
msgstr[0] "巴比伦甜菜炖肉"

#. ~ Conditional name for {'str': 'Babylonian beet stew', 'str_pl':
#. 'Babylonian beet stew'} when FLAG matches CANNIBALISM
#: .\items\comestibles\meat_dishes.json
msgid "Babe-lonian beet stew"
msgid_plural "Babes-lonian beet stew"
msgstr[0] "巴比伦甜菜炖肉"

#. ~ Conditional name for {'str': 'Babylonian beet stew', 'str_pl':
#. 'Babylonian beet stew'} when COMPONENT_ID matches mutant
#: .\items\comestibles\meat_dishes.json
msgid "ectoplasmic beet stew"
msgid_plural "ectoplasmic beet stew"
msgstr[0] "灵质甜菜炖肉"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Babylonian beet stew', 'str_pl': 'Babylonian
#. beet stew'}
#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Babylonian beet stew with couscous', 'str_pl':
#. 'Babylonian beet stews with couscous'}
#: .\items\comestibles\meat_dishes.json
msgid ""
"An ancient recipe, translated from a 4000 year old Babylonian clay tablet, "
"written in ancient Akkadian, consisting of beets, leeks, onions, garlic, "
"lamb, and spices, simmered in beer. Best eaten with couscous."
msgstr ""
"一道古老的食谱，译自一块4000年前的巴比伦泥板，用古阿卡德语书写，包含甜菜、韭葱、洋葱、大蒜、羊肉和香料，在啤酒中慢炖而成。最好搭配古斯米食用。"

#: .\items\comestibles\meat_dishes.json
msgid "clay pot rice"
msgid_plural "clay pot rice"
msgstr[0] "煲仔饭"

#. ~ Conditional name for {'str': 'clay pot rice', 'str_pl': 'clay pot rice'}
#. when FLAG matches CANNIBALISM
#: .\items\comestibles\meat_dishes.json
msgid "crackpot rice"
msgid_plural "crackpot rice"
msgstr[0] "煲仔饭"

#. ~ Conditional name for {'str': 'clay pot rice', 'str_pl': 'clay pot rice'}
#. when COMPONENT_ID matches mutant
#: .\items\comestibles\meat_dishes.json
msgid "corrupted clay pot rice"
msgid_plural "corrupted clay pot rice"
msgstr[0] "腐化煲仔饭"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'clay pot rice', 'str_pl': 'clay pot rice'}
#: .\items\comestibles\meat_dishes.json
msgid ""
"Rice, meat, veggies, and seasonings boiled together in a sealed clay pot "
"over a hot fire."
msgstr "米饭、肉类、蔬菜和调味料在密封的陶罐中用旺火一同炖煮而成。"

#: .\items\comestibles\meat_dishes.json
msgid "Babylonian beet stew with couscous"
msgid_plural "Babylonian beet stews with couscous"
msgstr[0] "巴比伦甜菜炖古斯米"

#. ~ Conditional name for {'str': 'Babylonian beet stew with couscous',
#. 'str_pl': 'Babylonian beet stews with couscous'} when FLAG matches
#. CANNIBALISM
#: .\items\comestibles\meat_dishes.json
msgid "Babe-lonian beet stew with couscous"
msgid_plural "Babes-lonian beet stews with couscous"
msgstr[0] "巴比伦甜菜炖古斯米"

#. ~ Conditional name for {'str': 'Babylonian beet stew with couscous',
#. 'str_pl': 'Babylonian beet stews with couscous'} when COMPONENT_ID matches
#. mutant
#: .\items\comestibles\meat_dishes.json
msgid "ectoplasmic beet stew with couscous"
msgid_plural "ectoplasmic beet stew with couscous"
msgstr[0] "灵质甜菜炖古斯米"

#: .\items\comestibles\spice.json
msgid "dehydrated mustard"
msgid_plural "dehydrated mustard"
msgstr[0] "脱水芥末酱"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'dehydrated mustard', 'str_pl': 'dehydrated
#. mustard'}
#: .\items\comestibles\spice.json
msgid ""
"Dehydrated prepared mustard. Can be reconstituted by just adding a bit of "
"water, but won't be as good as fresh mustard."
msgstr "脱水制备的芥末酱。只需加少许水即可复原，但风味不及新鲜芥末。"

#: .\items\comestibles\spice.json
msgid "ketjap manis"
msgid_plural "ketjap manis"
msgstr[0] "甜酱油"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'ketjap manis', 'str_pl': 'ketjap manis'}
#: .\items\comestibles\spice.json
msgid "Indonesian sweet soy sauce."
msgstr "印度尼西亚甜酱油。"

#: .\items\comestibles\spice.json
msgid "sambal"
msgid_plural "sambal"
msgstr[0] "叁巴酱"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'sambal', 'str_pl': 'sambal'}
#: .\items\comestibles\spice.json
msgid "Indo-Malay chilli paste."
msgstr "印度-马来风味辣椒酱。"

#: .\items\comestibles\veggy_dishes.json
msgid "pasta marinara"
msgid_plural "pasta marinara"
msgstr[0] "意式番茄酱面"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'pasta marinara', 'str_pl': 'pasta marinara'}
#: .\items\comestibles\veggy_dishes.json
msgid ""
"Cooked pasta with a jar of tomato sauce. Not very nutritious, but very easy "
"to make."
msgstr "煮熟的意大利面配上一罐番茄酱。营养不高，但制作非常简单。"

#: .\items\comestibles\veggy_dishes.json
msgid "pasta primavera"
msgid_plural "pasta primavera"
msgstr[0] "春季蔬菜意面"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'pasta primavera', 'str_pl': 'pasta primavera'}
#: .\items\comestibles\veggy_dishes.json
msgid "Pasta with sauteed veggies, spices, and olive oil."
msgstr "意面配以炒蔬菜、香料和橄榄油。"

#: .\items\comestibles\wheat.json
msgid "raw couscous pasta"
msgid_plural "raw couscous pasta"
msgstr[0] "生古斯米面"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'raw couscous pasta', 'str_pl': 'raw couscous
#. pasta'}
#: .\items\comestibles\wheat.json
msgid ""
"Durum semolina wheat flour dough, rubbed between the hands until it forms "
"small rice-like pellets. Could be eaten raw, but only takes a couple of "
"minutes to cook, so why bother?"
msgstr "硬质粗粒小麦粉面团，经手工揉搓成米粒状小颗粒。可以生吃，但只需几分钟就能煮熟，何必费事？"

#: .\items\comestibles\wheat.json
msgid "fun batter"
msgid_plural "fun batter"
msgstr[0] "肠粉浆"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'fun batter', 'str_pl': 'fun batter'}
#: .\items\comestibles\wheat.json
msgid ""
"A thin batter of rice and water, used to make rice noodle sheets called fun."
msgstr "由米和水调制的稀面糊，用于制作称为“肠粉”的米皮。"

#: .\items\comestibles\wheat.json
msgid "raw fun"
msgid_plural "raw fun"
msgstr[0] "生肠粉"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'raw fun', 'str_pl': 'raw fun'}
#: .\items\comestibles\wheat.json
msgid ""
"Thin, very wide Chinese rice noodles, made from a thin batter, steamed into "
"sheets then cut into wide strips."
msgstr "薄而宽的中国米线，由稀面糊制成，蒸成薄片后切成宽条。"

#: .\items\comestibles\wheat.json
msgid "prepared couscous"
msgid_plural "prepared couscous"
msgstr[0] "熟古斯米"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'prepared couscous', 'str_pl': 'prepared
#. couscous'}
#: .\items\comestibles\wheat.json
msgid ""
"Grain-like pasta cooked with broth. Delicious and filling, but not very "
"nutritious."
msgstr "用高汤煮熟的粒状意面。美味饱腹，但营养价值不高。"

#: .\items\comestibles\wheat.json
msgid "sooji halwa"
msgid_plural "sooji halwas"
msgstr[0] "粗麦粉哈尔瓦"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'sooji halwa', 'str_pl': 'sooji halwas'}
#: .\items\comestibles\wheat.json
msgid ""
"An Indian sweet consisting of couscous fried in butter or ghee, then cooked "
"with milk, sugar, and spices. Traditionally cut into diamond-shaped pieces."
msgstr "一种印度甜点，将古斯米用黄油或酥油炒制，然后与牛奶、糖和香料一同烹煮。传统上切成菱形块。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "rokushakubo"
msgid_plural "rokushakubos"
msgstr[0] "六尺棒"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'rokushakubo'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "A sturdy oak staff 6 shaku (180cm) in length."
msgstr "一根坚固的橡木长棍，长度为6尺（180厘米）。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "jyo"
msgid_plural "jyos"
msgstr[0] "杖"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'jyo'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "A sturdy oak staff 4 shaku (120cm) in length."
msgstr "一根坚固的橡木长棍，长度为4尺（120厘米）。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "hanbo"
msgid_plural "hanbos"
msgstr[0] "半棒"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'hanbo'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "A sturdy oak staff 3 shaku (90cm) in length."
msgstr "一根坚固的橡木短棍，长度为3尺（90厘米）。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "tanbo"
msgid_plural "tanbos"
msgstr[0] "短棒"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'tanbo'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "A sturdy oak staff 1 shaku (30cm) in length."
msgstr "一根坚固的橡木短棍，长度为1尺（30厘米）。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "dumbell bar"
msgid_plural "dumbell bars"
msgstr[0] "哑铃杆"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'dumbell bar'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "A heavy solid steel bar from a dumbell, 20cm in length."
msgstr "哑铃上的重型实心钢杆，长度为20厘米。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "barbell bar"
msgid_plural "barbell bars"
msgstr[0] "杠铃杆"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'barbell bar'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "A very heavy, solid steel bar from a barbell."
msgstr "杠铃上非常沉重的实心钢杆。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "hollow barbell bar"
msgid_plural "hollow barbell bars"
msgstr[0] "空心杠铃杆"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'hollow barbell bar'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid ""
"A lightweight hollow steel bar from a cheap barbell, reinforced with sturdy "
"plastic. As a weapon, it does little damage, but is very sturdy for its "
"weight, is light and fast, and has a long reach."
msgstr "廉价杠铃上的轻质空心钢杆，由坚固塑料加固。作为武器，它伤害较低，但以其重量而言非常坚固，轻便快速，且攻击范围长。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "putting trainer"
msgid_plural "putting trainers"
msgstr[0] "推杆训练器"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'putting trainer'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid ""
"A short section of a putter handle with a heavy weight on the end, for "
"training golfing techniques. Essentially a fairly sturdy mace."
msgstr "推杆手柄的一小段，末端带有重物，用于训练高尔夫技巧。本质上是一把相当坚固的钉头锤。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "jitte"
msgid_plural "jittes"
msgstr[0] "十手"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'jitte'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid ""
"The 'ten hands' weapon. A steel rod with a disarming hook, used primarily by"
" officers of the Edo police during the Edo period."
msgstr "“十手”武器。一种带有卸械钩的钢棍，主要供江户时代的警察官员使用。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "tokushukeibo"
msgid_plural "tokushukeibos"
msgstr[0] "特缩警棒"

#. ~ Use action menu_text for {'str': 'tokushukeibo'}.
#. ~ Use action menu_text for {'str': 'tokushukeibo jitte'}.
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "Expand"
msgstr "展开"

#. ~ Use action msg for {'str': 'tokushukeibo'}.
#. ~ Use action msg for {'str': 'tokushukeibo jitte'}.
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "You snap open your tokushukeibo."
msgstr "你啪地一声展开了特缩警棒。"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'tokushukeibo'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid ""
"Steel cobra, a telescoping lightweight spring steel rod with a weighted tip,"
" that collapses for easy storage.  Makes an excellent melee weapon.  "
"Activate to expand."
msgstr "钢蛇，一种可伸缩的轻质弹簧钢杆，带有加重尖端，可折叠便于存放。是极佳的近战武器。激活以展开。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "tokushukeibo (extended)"
msgid_plural "tokushukeibo (extended)"
msgstr[0] "特缩警棒（展开状态）"

#. ~ Use action menu_text for {'str': 'tokushukeibo (extended)', 'str_pl':
#. 'tokushukeibo (extended)'}.
#. ~ Use action menu_text for {'str': 'tokushukeibo jitte (extended)',
#. 'str_pl': 'tokushukeibo jitte (extended)'}.
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "Collapse"
msgstr "收缩"

#. ~ Use action msg for {'str': 'tokushukeibo (extended)', 'str_pl':
#. 'tokushukeibo (extended)'}.
#. ~ Use action msg for {'str': 'tokushukeibo jitte (extended)', 'str_pl':
#. 'tokushukeibo jitte (extended)'}.
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "You collapse your tokushukeibo."
msgstr "你收起了特缩警棒。"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'tokushukeibo (extended)', 'str_pl':
#. 'tokushukeibo (extended)'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid ""
"A steel cobra baton that collapses for easy storage.  Makes an excellent "
"melee weapon.  Activate to collapse."
msgstr "一种可折叠的钢制眼镜蛇警棍，便于收纳。是出色的近战武器。激活以折叠。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "tokushukeibo jitte"
msgid_plural "tokushukeibo jittes"
msgstr[0] "特修警棍 十手"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'tokushukeibo jitte'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid ""
"Steel cobra, a telescoping lightweight spring steel rod with a weighted tip "
"and a disarming hook, that collapses for easy storage.  Makes an excellent "
"melee weapon.  Activate to expand."
msgstr "钢制眼镜蛇，一种可伸缩的轻质弹簧钢杆，带有加重尖端和缴械钩，可折叠以便收纳。是出色的近战武器。激活以展开。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "tokushukeibo jitte (extended)"
msgid_plural "tokushukeibo jitte (extended)"
msgstr[0] "特修警棍 十手（展开状态）"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'tokushukeibo jitte (extended)', 'str_pl':
#. 'tokushukeibo jitte (extended)'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid ""
"A steel cobra baton with a disarming hook, that collapses for easy storage."
"  Makes an excellent melee weapon.  Activate to collapse."
msgstr "一种带有缴械钩的钢制眼镜蛇警棍，可折叠以便收纳。是出色的近战武器。激活以折叠。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "fake tessen"
msgid_plural "fake tessens"
msgstr[0] "仿制铁扇"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'fake tessen'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid ""
"An iron fan, a small steel bludgeon designed to resemble a folded hand fan, "
"carried by Samurai in situations in which wearing a sword was not permitted."
" This one is purely a weapon, and not functional as a fan."
msgstr "一把铁扇，一种小型钢制钝器，设计成折叠手扇的形状，由武士在禁止佩剑的场合携带。此物纯粹是武器，不具备扇子的功能。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "tessen"
msgid_plural "tessens"
msgstr[0] "铁扇"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'tessen'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid ""
"An iron fan, a rice paper hand fan with a sturdy steel frame and steel or "
"bamboo ribs, carried by Samurai in situations in which wearing a sword was "
"not permitted. This one is also functional as a fan."
msgstr "一把铁扇，一把宣纸手扇，配有坚固的钢制框架和钢制或竹制扇骨，由武士在禁止佩剑的场合携带。此物也可作为扇子使用。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "bonker"
msgid_plural "bonkers"
msgstr[0] "敲鱼棒"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'bonker'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "A small wooden club for stunning fish."
msgstr "一根用于击晕鱼类的小木棒。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "manriki gusari"
msgid_plural "manriki gusaris"
msgstr[0] "万力锁链"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'manriki gusari'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "A heavy steel chain with a weighted grip on each end."
msgstr "一根沉重的钢链，两端各有一个加重的握柄。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "keychain"
msgid_plural "keychains"
msgstr[0] "钥匙链"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'keychain'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid ""
"A big, heavy bunch of keys on the end of a steel chain. Makes a fairly "
"effective flail."
msgstr "钢链末端挂着一大串沉重钥匙。是相当有效的连枷武器。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "blackthorn stick"
msgid_plural "blackthorn sticks"
msgstr[0] "黑刺李手杖"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'blackthorn stick'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid ""
"A walking stick made from a sapling of dense blackthorn or sloe wood, with a"
" large knob at the top, that has been left to cure in a chimney.  A "
"traditional Irish weapon derived from the shillelagh."
msgstr "一根由致密黑刺李或黑刺李木幼树制成的手杖，顶部有一个大圆头，曾在烟囱中风干。这是一种源自爱尔兰短棍的传统爱尔兰武器。"

#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid "synthetic blackthorn stick"
msgid_plural "synthetic blackthorn sticks"
msgstr[0] "合成黑刺李手杖"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'synthetic blackthorn stick'}
#: .\items\melee\bludgeons.json
msgid ""
"A walking stick made from a sapling of dense blackthorn or sloe wood, with a"
" large knob at the top, that has been left to cure in a chimney.  A "
"traditional Irish weapon derived from the shillelagh. This is a synthetic "
"one made from durable polymer, cheaper and more durable than a wooden one, "
"but less effective as a weapon."
msgstr ""
"一根由致密黑刺李或黑刺李木幼树制成的手杖，顶部有一个大圆头，曾在烟囱中风干。这是一种源自爱尔兰短棍的传统爱尔兰武器。这是一把由耐用聚合物制成的合成品，比木制的更便宜、更耐用，但作为武器的效果稍差。"

#: .\items\melee\spears_and_polearms.json
msgid "guandao"
msgid_plural "guandaos"
msgstr[0] "关刀"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'guandao'}
#: .\items\melee\spears_and_polearms.json
msgid ""
"This is a giant ancient Chinese battlefield polearm, named for its purported"
" inventor, the legendary 3rd century general Guan Yu. Though it may have "
"never existed, the original was thought to have weighed as much as 49kg, and"
" required great strength to wield, but by the time of the earliest confirmed"
" records of the weapon, the design had already shed much of its weight, "
"while retaining its imposing size. This is a modern version, weighing in at "
"10kg."
msgstr ""
"这是一种巨大的中国古代战场长柄武器，以其传说中的发明者——公元3世纪的传奇将领关羽命名。尽管它可能从未存在过，但据信原重可达49公斤，需要极大的力量才能挥舞；然而，到该武器最早的确切记载出现时，其设计已大幅减重，同时保留了其庞大的尺寸。这是一个现代版本，重10公斤。"

#: .\items\melee\spears_and_polearms.json
msgid "qinglong yanyuedao"
msgid_plural "qinglong yanyuedaos"
msgstr[0] "青龙偃月刀"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'qinglong yanyuedao'}
#: .\items\melee\spears_and_polearms.json
msgid ""
"This is a giant ancient Chinese battlefield polearm, named for its purported"
" inventor, the legendary 3rd century general Guan Yu. Though it may have "
"never existed, the original was thought to have weighed as much as 49kg, and"
" required great strength to wield, but by the time of the earliest confirmed"
" records of the weapon, the design had already shed much of its weight, "
"while retaining its imposing size. This is a faithful reproduction of Guan "
"Yu's own weapon, the Qinglong Yanyuedao or Green Dragon Crescent Blade."
msgstr ""
"这是一种巨大的中国古代战场长柄武器，以其传说中的发明者——公元3世纪的传奇将领关羽命名。尽管它可能从未存在过，但据信原重可达49公斤，需要极大的力量才能挥舞；然而，到该武器最早的确切记载出现时，其设计已大幅减重，同时保留了其庞大的尺寸。这是对关羽本人的武器——青龙偃月刀的忠实复刻。"

#: .\items\melee\spears_and_polearms.json
msgid "bisento"
msgid_plural "bisentos"
msgstr[0] "眉尖刀"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'bisento'}
#: .\items\melee\spears_and_polearms.json
msgid ""
"The Japanese equivalent of the guandao. Pretty much a direct copy of the "
"guandao design, but forged with the same forging techniques that created the"
" katana. Heftier than a modern guandao, the bisento requires considerable "
"strength to wield, while techniques focus on keeping the blade in constant "
"motion using the whole body, and using its weight to increase attacking "
"power."
msgstr ""
"关刀的日本对应物。几乎是关刀设计的直接复制品，但采用了与打造武士刀相同的锻造技术。比现代关刀更重，眉尖刀需要相当大的力量才能挥舞，其技巧侧重于利用全身使刀锋保持持续运动，并利用其重量增加攻击力。"

#: .\items\melee\spears_and_polearms.json
msgid "dragon qiang"
msgid_plural "dragon qiangs"
msgstr[0] "龙枪"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'dragon qiang'}
#: .\items\melee\spears_and_polearms.json
msgid ""
"A mythical Chinese spear, consisting of a solid steel, textured shaft with a"
" diamond-shaped spear point. Equally effective at bashing and stabbing, but "
"heavy and slow."
msgstr "一种神话般的中国长枪，由实心钢制纹理枪杆和菱形枪尖组成。在打击和刺击方面同样有效，但沉重且缓慢。"

#: .\items\melee\swords_and_blades.json
msgid "grosse messer"
msgid_plural "grosse messers"
msgstr[0] "大砍刀"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'grosse messer'}
#: .\items\melee\swords_and_blades.json
msgid ""
"A large single-edged two-handed sword from Germany, resembling an oversized "
"kitchen knife. The name means Big Knife."
msgstr "一种来自德国的大型单刃双手剑，形似一把超大号的菜刀。其名称意为“大刀”。"

#: .\items\melee\swords_and_blades.json
msgid "da dao"
msgid_plural "da daos"
msgstr[0] "大刀"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'da dao'}
#: .\items\melee\swords_and_blades.json
msgid ""
"This is a heavy two-handed Chinese ring-pommeled sabre with a short, wide "
"blade and S crossguard. It hits almost as hard as a greatsword or claymore, "
"but is much easier to use. The lack of reach is a disadvantage on the "
"battlefield, but an advantage in tight spaces."
msgstr ""
"这是一把沉重的中国双手环首大刀，刀身短而宽，配有S形护手。其打击力几乎与巨剑或克莱莫剑相当，但更易于使用。攻击距离短是战场上的劣势，但在狭窄空间中是优势。"

#: .\items\melee\swords_and_blades.json
msgid "rebar sword"
msgid_plural "rebar swords"
msgstr[0] "钢筋剑"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'rebar sword'}
#: .\items\melee\swords_and_blades.json
msgid ""
"A large, heavy sword-shaped cudgel forged from rebar, with a dull edge and "
"sharp tip, and a flat disc or square crossguard."
msgstr "一把由钢筋锻造的大型沉重剑形棍棒，刃口钝，尖端锋利，配有扁平圆盘或方形护手。"

#: .\items\melee\swords_and_blades.json
msgid "pudao"
msgid_plural "pudao"
msgstr[0] "朴刀"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'pudao', 'str_pl': 'pudao'}
#: .\items\melee\swords_and_blades.json
msgid ""
"A Chinese long-handled sword with a single-edged curved blade, consisting of"
" a dao blade attached to a medium length pole, extending its reach and "
"increasing damage and attack speed with a minimal increase in weight."
msgstr "一种中国长柄刀，单刃曲刀，由一把刀身连接到中等长度的杆上构成，延伸了攻击距离，并在重量增加最小的情况下提高了伤害和攻击速度。"

#: .\items\melee\swords_and_blades.json
msgid "nagamaki"
msgid_plural "nagamaki"
msgstr[0] "长卷"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'nagamaki', 'str_pl': 'nagamaki'}
#: .\items\melee\swords_and_blades.json
msgid ""
"A long-handled tachi sword from Japan, likely evolved from the Chinese "
"pudao, and the ancestor of the naginata."
msgstr "一种来自日本的长柄太刀，可能由中国朴刀演变而来，是薙刀的前身。"

#: .\items\tool\cooking.json
msgid "fun pan"
msgid_plural "fun pans"
msgstr[0] "粉盘"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'fun pan'}
#: .\items\tool\cooking.json
msgid ""
"A flat steaming pan, with a lid and an internal pan, for making sheets of "
"rice noodles known as fun."
msgstr "一个扁平的蒸盘，带有盖子和内盘，用于制作称为“粉”的米粉皮。"

#: .\items\vehicle\wheel.json
msgid "60 inch industrial off-road wheel"
msgid_plural "60 inch industrial off-road wheels"
msgstr[0] "60英寸工业越野车轮"

#. ~ Description for {'str': '60 inch industrial off-road wheel'}
#: .\items\vehicle\wheel.json
msgid ""
"A 60-inch diameter, wide off-road wheel, used in mining, forestry, and "
"military transport."
msgstr "一个直径60英寸的宽大越野车轮，用于采矿、林业和军事运输。"
